      "span_text": "Another reason why skaters experience lower back pain is thought to be the presence of secondary hip-spine syndrome, [CITATION_4] and the lumbar flexure caused by tightness of the iliopsoas muscle and the limitation of hip extension. Our hypothesis is that the limitation of hip extension while skating results in anterior inclination of the pelvis, which enhances lumbar flexure, thus causing lower back pain."
